Set the Interactive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on and Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on parameters by performing the following steps:1) From the domain controller, open the Group Policy Management Editor focused on the appropriate Domain, OU(s) and/or GPOs within Active Directory depending on OU architecture;2) Navigate to the following subtree - Computer Configuration\Policies\Windows Settings\Security Settings\Local Policies\Security Options;3) Set the Interactive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on value in accordance with corporate standards or the recommendation in the control procedure;4) Set the Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on value in accordance with corporate standards or the recommendation in the control procedure;5) Click OK to confirm changes; and6) Close the Group Policy Management Editor.
